RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 84. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE NOVEMBER 19, 2022 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SECRET LIFE STYLE saved ground while being unhurried, angled out nearing the eighth pole to be four-wide and was up in the final sixteenth to win going away. PRINCE OF LUCK stalked the pace while two-wide, moved out to be three-wide nearing the quarter pole and closed strongly. BESAME MUCHO vied for the early lead from along the inside, opened a clear lead nearing the quarter pole but was unable to resist the top two late while holding on fairly well for third. ANNA'S IRON MAN vied for the early lead from between horses, dropped back slightly nearing the five-sixteenths pole, angled in but lacked a late response. MANAALABOUTDAMONEY vied for the lead to near the quarter pole while three-wide and tired. OXBOW PARK dropped back while racing three-wide and failed to threaten.

ENTRY.OWNER: Evans Justin R Tomasic Bill and Tomasic Susan

ENTRY.NAME: Secret Life Style
ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried, saved ground, angled out 4-w 1/8, up final 1/16

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MR. BUGS broke in then moved up to vie with LET GEORGE DO IT, disposed of that one before going three furlongs, opened a clear lead and maintained a safe advantage. SMILING PREACHER stalked the pace while racing three-wide, offered a bid entering the stretch, could not reach the winner but finished well for second. EXIT STAGE LEFT was allowed to settle early, came three-wide into the stretch and finished in a mild rally. POCO DIABLO ROJO was reserved off the early pace, came four-wide into the stretch and failed to seriously threaten. LET GEORGE DO IT vied for the lead for three furlongs and gave way. RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 69. Maiden Special Weight Purse 24000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHANCELLORS BOOM sprinted clear early, saved ground setting the pace and drew off to win as the rider pleased. DYNAMIC SECRET broke in to brush with CALORESE, then chased the winner while racing two-wide, could not reach the winner but finished well for second. ALLANTE was allowed to settle in stride, came three-wide into the stretch and finished in a mild rally. WHEREVER YOU ARE saved ground while being prominently placed into the stretch and ended up in a dead-heat for fourth with WELL IMAGINE THAT while weakening late. WELL IMAGINE THAT was unhurried early, came three-wide into the stretch and finished on even terms with WHEREVER YOU ARE while gaining slightly late. CALORESE was off a step slow and then brushed shortly after the start, dropped back, came five-wide into the stretch and failed to menace. BOSSYBYNATURE broke out then showed brief speed from between horses and gave way.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SUPER CLASSIC was prominent from the outset while racing three-wide, moved up to take the lead nearing the eighth pole and gradually drew clear. MARKSMAN ON TARGET saved ground setting the pace, responded when headed, could not stay with the winner but continued on gamely for second. THIRSTY KISS saved ground while being allowed to settle, angled out to come three-wide into the stretch, offered a bid nearing the eighth pole and then flattened out. WARRIORS HERO was reserved off the early pace while racing three-wide, came four-wide into the stretch but lacked a rally. RACE.FOOTNOTES: DRAGON WORKS saved ground while being allowed to settle, came three-wide into the stretch, ran down SENSIBLE LUTE to take the lead at the sixteenth pole and quickly drew clear. ENGLISH MEADOW was unhurried early, rallied four-wide into the stretch and finished full of run. SQUARE FUN was bumped at the start by POCKET KNIFE, then was forwardly placed to the stretch while two-wide and weakened. CAPE UNION was reserved early, steadied from between horses nearing the seven-sixteenths pole, then angled in to save ground and improved his position. POCKET KNIFE broke out to bump SQUARE FUN, then dropped back, came five-wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. NATION'S BELLE prompted the early pace while racing three-wide and tired. LIBBY'S GAMBIT settled in the middle of the field, steadied and was shuffled back nearing the five-sixteenths pole and was unable to recover.
